Strcmp.description: In ML-KEM.Decaps the ciphertext is compared with the output of K-PKE.Encrypt for implicit rejection. If an implementation were to use strcmp() for that comparison it would fail to reject some ciphertexts if a zero byte terminates the comparison early. The chance of it occurring randomly is 2⁻¹⁶. These vectors are valid and test that the implicit rejection path is taken as expected.

ModulusOverflow.description: These encapsulation keys have polynomial coefficients that overflow the field prime and should fail the Modulus check of Section 7.2 of FIPS 203.
